The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 27: Indias largest ever offering of oil and gas exploration areas will close on Monday with only a few big international players such as ENI of Italy, BG and BP Plc likely to bid because of the controversy over tax breaks. The seventh round of bid under New Exploration Licensing Policy, where 57 blocks were offered, would close at 1200 hours on June 30.                            
	 Tokyo, June 27: Daiichi Sankyo may sell debt to raise half the cost of its $4.6 billion acquisition of Ranbaxy Laboratories.                             
	 New Delhi, June 27: India and Pakistan have resolved all bilateral commercial issues impeding implementation of the $7.4-billion gas pipeline from Iran and will jointly address Tehrans demand for price revision.                            
	 New Delhi, June 27: The RBI has allowed charitable trusts and societies to invest in other countries through joint ventures and wholly owned subsidiaries, a move that is likely to help organisations to set up their branches abroad.                             
	 New Delhi, June 27: Basmati rice exporter Kohinoor Foods, which is facing a hostile takeover by Temptation Foods Ltd, has got a major reprieve with the Company Law Board restraining latters voting rights on the basis of shares acquired by it.
                                                                                                                               
